Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells with LaSr2Fe2CrO9-delta-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta composite anodes were tested in H-2, H2S-contaminated H-2, and CH4 fuels as well as under redox cycling conditions.
Titulo: Structural, chemical, and electrochemical characteristics of LaSr2Fe2CrO9-δ-based solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: The La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta electrolyte supported cells had La0.4Ce0.6O2-delta barrier layers to prevent cation diffusion between LaSr2Fe2CrO9-delta and La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta.
Titulo: Structural, chemical, and electrochemical characteristics of LaSr2Fe2CrO9-δ-based solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: After an initial break-in where the performance improved slightly, the cells were stable in humidified H-2 with a power density >0.4W
